      "writtenOn": "2018-02-21T17:24:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Whats the lifetime of this? can texture*Proc be called multiple times? How does client know when it can delete textureContext? Maybe textureFulfill and textureReleaseProc could be std::functions() and client can rely on destructors to delete whatever heap allocations might be buried beneath?",
      "range": {
